data.meta_description: Twelve boys, members of the Friendly Indians YMCA youth group, one posing with drum, one with single-feather headband.  Back row (left to right): Richard Swartz (1928-1957), Bob Swartz (1928-2007), Irving Johnson (1928-1950), Dick Hopkins, Gene Frost (1928-1996), unidentified.  Front row (left to right): first 4 unidentified, Jim Summers (right of drummer), unidentified. Group adviser was Reverend Marvin Davis.  Verso of photograph reads: "Leroy Konkel is here -- but not identified." Konkel, Curtis Leroy, 1927-2009.
